  "implementationNotes": [
    "Turret talents no longer mutate the owning actor defense/actions through stale ActiveEffects; they are action/reference cards until a turret actor subsystem owns the created turret.",
    "Jumptrooper and Advance Patrol contextual movement/surprise/initiative talents no longer apply always-on attack, skill, or Reflex bonuses.",
    "Critical Master riders now use a lightweight rule path that exposes targetEffectsOnCritical on attack cards; final target mutation remains GM/runtime-applied.",
    "Weapon Master selected-choice hit riders expose DR/DT adjustments on attack cards without permanent sheet mutation.",
    "Greater Weapon Focus/Specialization use safe selected-choice roll-context modifiers, so they only apply when the chosen weapon group/exotic weapon matches the rolled weapon.",
    "Carbineer, Pistoleer, Vanguard, Republic Commando combat options use CombatOptionResolver flags/options where existing context is sufficient."
  ],
